author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
Grocery prices are on the rise, and early evidence suggests President Trump’s tariffs aren’t helping. Pineapples from Costa Rica, fish from Greece and cheese from Italy are all subject to Trump’s tariffs, but that doesn’t mean customers are seeing the price increases–yet. 

WSJ visited the grocery store chain Stew Leonard’s and spoke with the CEO to see how tariffs are affecting a handful of popular items.
